{"title":"Evaluating and Improving Factuality in Multimodal Abstractive Summarization","domain":"MULTIMODAL","seeds":[{"problem":"Existing factuality metrics for abstractive summarization correlate well with human judgments on text-only inputs but ignore the vision modality, making them unreliable for multimodal (image+text) summarization.","method":"Propose CLIPBERTSCORE, a zero-shot multimodal factuality metric that combines image–summary similarity from CLIPScore (using CLIP RN50x64) with document–summary precision from BERTScore (using RoBERTa-large-MNLI), aggregated via a tunable weighted sum α (α=0.25 tuned on validation). This simple combination outperforms text-only baselines and an existing multimodal metric (MMAE) and matches fine-tuned alternatives on combined judgments, while remaining robust across MUFAME, WikiHowFact, FOIL, BISON, and FRANK benchmarks."},{"problem":"There is no meta-evaluation benchmark with human judgments to assess multimodal factuality metrics that must consider both document and image consistency.","method":"Create MUFAME, a step-level WikiHow-based meta-evaluation with AMT annotations that separately label factuality w.r.t. the document and the image and define a combined judgment; also introduce WikiHowFact, a ranking task that requires selecting the correct summary from distractors under document-only, image-only, or combined prompts. Use MUFAME to tune CLIPBERTSCORE’s α and show higher correlations with human judgments than text-only metrics and MMAE, and competitive performance with a fine-tuned triplet network."},{"problem":"Multimodal summarization models can hallucinate and underutilize visual information; practical training methods are needed to improve factuality with respect to both text and images.","method":"Leverage CLIPBERTSCORE as a training signal in two ways: (1) Visual guidance—rank and select important images via CLIPBERTSCORE and add an auxiliary guidance loss to encourage attention to selected images, improving image precision and factuality metrics on MSMO with minimal ROUGE trade-off; (2) Self-critical sequence training—use CLIPBERTSCORE (upweighted) alternated with ROUGE-2 as rewards under REINFORCE (high RL weight), yielding consistent gains in BERTScore, FactCC, DAE, and QuestEval on MMSS/MSMO and statistically significant human-rated factuality improvements."}]}
